Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have problems with overweight, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles, current research shows.
It shows again what is the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
Obsessed children feed on sausages at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had dined fries the day before the test, which is linked to the "Obesity is not a coincidence" prevention program.
In families of overweight children there is no custom of playing sports, which is applicable to most families today, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and nearly 900 Basic Education children from all over the Czech Republic participated in it.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th year.
A proper diet and enough exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obese children.
“Only half of the children surveyed have answered that they have five meals a day depending on the diet: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” the study said.
No breakfast but with sausage for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, the details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast as a family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to discover that in 10% of households nothing is eaten for breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that unhealthy fries are consumed much more frequently in families of obese children.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen kids (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal."
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets.
“The popularity of soft drinks is especially alarming,” the study’s final report warns.
As a main meal, the palm takes the pasta and the poultry closely follows.
Practically, children always reject legume and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switch to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases an important change in favor of the principles of healthy eating," says the study results.
Attention is drawn, for example, to sweet sodas, where many children would begin to prefer ordinary water.
Children would also more often choose poultry and fish for the main meal in the questionnaire and restrict consumption of sweet foods and flour products.
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, professionals say.
In the introductory article, How Stylists Learn, I already complained a bit that the initial lessons were already quite loaded.
I had no idea how that would go.
Lectures by three professionals in the field, how to dress problematic characters and, in addition, a seminar on how it works in show business.
And it'll be worse.
The closer the final exams are, the more information and practical tasks await us.
And although the course runs every Saturday and Sunday, there is no longer a pin.
We have studied with the director, Alena, (in the course there is no man) on how to dress the woman who does not have perfect symmetry.
And so is the vast majority.
Someone is short-necked, someone has a stylized figure without the right curves and someone is overweight.
The stylist must know how to optically soften wide shoulders, lengthen a neck or recreate the necessary curves.
We have been given some tricks on how to make the body of women of the type of Jennifer Lopez stand out, with huge breasts and hips but narrow waist and at the same time not dress it in a way too challenging
If, for example, the difference between the waist and hips is so large that the skirt or pants do not fit, it is worth getting at least one extra piece of fabric sewn to size.
You will certainly not regret it, because clothing that feels perfectly is priceless.
With a tailored skirt you will feel much better than with one that does not stop moving, getting up, dancing at the waist, etc.
The stylized body can be allowed to wear clothes with folds, ornaments, embroidery or drapes.
There are certainly many different types of information and bodies, so I am happy that I have all week to get all this information in my head.
And even so, I'm afraid with the task assigned, I already have more than enough.
Each participant in the course has been assigned two celebrities, to whom you must design two costumes: one for the day and one for the night.
You have to take into account the current appearance, the fashion style that suits the person in question.
I've had to "dress" Miranda Kerr, maybe you know her from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
I scream inside, for me it is much better than, for example, Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who lately will have gained a hundred kilos (please take into account the exaggeration), or the very young Selena Gomez.
The dresses have to be cut out of magazines or searched on the internet and printed, and then made graphically.
The moodboard, which is what the full result is called, also expresses our personal style and our relationship with graphic design.
It is also important to think about the graphic part of the styling.
The stylist, therefore, not only dresses physically, but also deals, for example, with the pages of products in magazines (of specific topics, such as trends, bags, coats, etc.).
All of this was discussed by stylist and designer Mario Kameník.
But all of this is over by Sunday.
The stylist must have a global vision.
The three invited specialists animated Saturday’s conference with information on all kinds of bodies.
Fashion designer Jakub Polanka, stylist Honza Pokorn and fashion photographer Ben Ren.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to take advantage of this.
And a good stylist knows how to work with the same garment in different ways.
Variability is, in this case, fundamental.
Thus, this trench coat (or as they say in English, trench-coat) can be dressed to the classic with jeans and t-shirt, but it also serves to dress the naked body with high-heeled shoes and photograph it as if it were actually a dress.
Or just roll it up and raise your neck to get a totally different image.
“Play with it,” he insisted.
What I value the most is the following advice: "To start working, you need to know all the rules first."
“Then you can break them,” Jakub said.
It is finally clear to me why we memorize all these formulas, what is combined with what, why, if later it turns out that in fashion magazines we find different results.
Not to mention the parades.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know that a stylist has to have more types of clothes in stock than he intends to photograph.
Thus, for a fashion story that has ten pages (therefore, ten outfits), you have to have prepared, ready to use, at least fifteen.
And besides that the photos the clothes work in combination with other garments, all of them different from those used in reality.
All this must be taken into account when designing the outfit.
Honza Pokorn assured us that the image and the style represent themselves, in many cases, half of the success.
It is enough to look at Madonna, who is not exactly an extraordinary singer, but the image and the marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, at the moment, there is not yet a clear tendency to use the services of stylists.
Even famous people find it useless (my abilities are enough, my physical appearance is not so important).
And when someone asks us for our services, we must bear in mind that it is very likely that they indicate a very different size from their real (lesser).
Then it is only left to guggle and find out if the magazines of the heart have already written on the subject, if a certain celebrity has gained/thinned, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario insisted that the stylist is not enough to orient himself in fashion, but has to understand outfit.
During your work, you should especially communicate with the people you saw, so it is essential to be a good psychologist.
He knows how to value people, he does not miss them, he defends their opinions.
“When a director hires you to sort her wardrobe and complete it with nice clothes, you can’t take and throw everything away and say, ‘Fuck off.’ ”
“Find at least a couple of things you can ponder and recommend so someone can put them on,” says Mario.
He himself also showed us that everything must fit into the so-called "placovka", that is, the job board.
This is fixed around the waist and you have all the necessary tools there.
There is also nylon thread (which serves the stylist during the photo shoot of products such as bags or hats), special clothespins in front, if this is larger (pins and other hooks are not allowed, they could damage the fabric), or a sewing set.
In order not to stay in passive listening and put something into practice, we have learned to coat the soles of the shoes.
Even during photo shoots in the studio, on a flat surface, you could damage the sole and much more outside.
And we did nothing but clothe and clothe.
We could not touch the shoes with the scissors so as not to damage them by accident.
So you had to be very skilled.
Mario has given me a joy in praising my work unreservedly.
The truth is, I'm not very good at those skills.
This is just a small part of everything we’ve heard all weekend, in the second part of the course.
I’ve already realized that professional hairstyling isn’t a pink road, but I don’t care what people say.
Need for Speed: The Run is racing across America.
Review
A journey, at first carefree, is complicated by a series of carelessness unbecoming of a routine journey during tomorrow’s shift.
To some extent it was possible to meet expectations, but this is of no use, if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended.
The new installment, to which the title is added, aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
It promised that it would give new airs to the old saga of races Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, it appears as a game that should not end up again being an action genre without more.
We were also curious to know what the inserted scenes would look like, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality they cannot even be called errors, but rather it is the incomprehensible reluctance of the programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first ones to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place along a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the chart is equivalent to that of previous installments in the series.
It is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumnal landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you have to be careful so that an avalanche does not bury you.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required amount of opponents (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the midst of all this, the police sometimes appear, which only makes things more difficult.
What’s new is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button just at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It’s surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you’d expect (specifically there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the aforementioned context, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big thing, but it cannot be said that it is bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of the driving models, the same is no longer true with collisions.
Of games of this type you can not expect it to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when doing a very tight overtaking or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resets are available for each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something does not go well, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, not even reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage by heart.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civilian" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes rage especially in situations, when you see that two cars that are going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your nose.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always overtake you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can mush the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you will surely be disappointed right away.
And it’s a shame, because although the model of the journey is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit gets the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so it doesn’t fit boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during races.
You have to keep an eye on the gas pumps next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases what you have will be enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supercars for technical driving, for example on curved mountain roads.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both the challenges and the stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community features available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you reach the subway tunnel (passage), where you start to run in the dark along the tracks (passage).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km / h (pass) and, suddenly, from behind you the convoy of the metro arrives and takes you ahead without more.
In the newsroom we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects are in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
Well, it is a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where there are many participants involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and his mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game is not over.
The fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
