The Ambassador to the EU, Vicenová:
Czechs have a reputation for being negative and Eurosceptic.
"The Lisbon Treaty has significantly affected the balance between individual institutions"
“I didn’t expect an all-out war to be mounted.”
"It will take five, six years, before the situation stabilizes a little, calms down and new players get used to their new roles," Czech Ambassador to the EU Milena Vicenová began her lecture at the Faculty of Law with conviction.
How not to take seriously his motto "clear and open about Europe", which he said already in the first part of his lecture, when he managed to describe each EU body and its relations with such precision and clarity, because it would be the envy of many lecturers of the Faculty of Law of the U. Carolina.
