This was the work of the caleño who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lophoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4th, a lophoscopist from Cali’s CTI went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the FARC’s top leader: “Alfonso Cano,” through the collation of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists who work in the section of the CTI, that week it was the turn of “availability” to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to go into the jungle for more than five days to reach the site where the bodies that had to be identified were.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of friction skin, that is, the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothing for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for El Cauca by helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadactyl card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigation team at the site where the body was, he did not recognize it because of its physical appearance, since it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local farmer, without glasses and much thinner.
But the footprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the head of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a dactiloscopista of the Sijin of Cali, the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know our job.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become key in solving crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, lophoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the people captured.
When caught, many criminals present fake IDs or do not have papers.
We take their fingerprints and look them up in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“Walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to get a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts,” he recalled.
Fingerprints can also rule out or reaffirm suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
The investigation determined that a family member could be a suspect in the crime and, indeed, a print on the bottle matched.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the murderer, it does place him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI fingerprintist explained that in objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” said the CTI expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI TV show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes an imprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective matching is performed.
